				<div id="bodyContent" class="vector-body" aria-labelledby="firstHeading" data-mw-ve-target-container>
					<div class="vector-body-before-content">
							<div class="mw-indicators">
		</div>

						<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
					</div>
					<div id="contentSub"><div id="mw-content-subtitle"></div></div>
					
					
					<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang="en" dir="ltr"><p class="mw-empty-elt">
</p>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Peter_Paul_Rubens_-_Annunciation_-_WGA20250.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9f/Peter_Paul_Rubens_-_Annunciation_-_WGA20250.jpg/220px-Peter_Paul_Rubens_-_Annunciation_-_WGA20250.jpg" decoding="async" width="220" height="340" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9f/Peter_Paul_Rubens_-_Annunciation_-_WGA20250.jpg/330px-Peter_Paul_Rubens_-_Annunciation_-_WGA20250.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9f/Peter_Paul_Rubens_-_Annunciation_-_WGA20250.jpg/440px-Peter_Paul_Rubens_-_Annunciation_-_WGA20250.jpg 2x" data-file-width="876" data-file-height="1353" /></a><figcaption>The Holy Spirit as a dove in the <a href="/wiki/Annunciation" title="Annunciation">Annunciation</a> by <a href="/wiki/Rubens" class="mw-redirect" title="Rubens">Rubens</a>, 1628</figcaption></figure>
<p>The <a href="/wiki/Holy_Spirit_(Christianity)" class="mw-redirect" title="Holy Spirit (Christianity)">Holy Spirit</a> has been represented in <a href="/wiki/Christian_art" title="Christian art">Christian art</a> both in the <a href="/wiki/Eastern_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="Eastern Church">Eastern</a> and <a href="/wiki/Western_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="Western Church">Western Churches</a> using a variety of depictions.<sup id="cite_ref-Earls70_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Earls70-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-Gardner349_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Gardner349-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-Lossky_3-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Lossky-3">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>The depictions have ranged from nearly identical figures that represent the three persons of the <a href="/wiki/Holy_Trinity" class="mw-redirect" title="Holy Trinity">Holy Trinity</a> from a dove to a flame.<sup id="cite_ref-Eugene121_4-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Eugene121-4">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>The Holy Spirit is often depicted as a <a href="/wiki/Dove" class="mw-redirect" title="Dove">dove</a>, based on the account of the Holy Spirit descending like a dove on <a href="/wiki/Baptism_of_Jesus" title="Baptism of Jesus">Jesus at his baptism</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-Joel14_5-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Joel14-5">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> In many paintings of the <a href="/wiki/Annunciation" title="Annunciation">Annunciation</a>, the Holy Spirit is shown in the form of a dove, coming down towards Mary on beams of light, as the <a href="/wiki/Gabriel" title="Gabriel">Archangel Gabriel</a> announces <a href="/wiki/Christ" class="mw-redirect" title="Christ">Christ</a>'s coming to <a href="/wiki/Mary,_the_mother_of_Jesus" class="mw-redirect" title="Mary, the mother of Jesus">Mary</a>.
</p><p>A dove may also be seen at the ear of <a href="/wiki/Saint_Gregory_the_Great" class="mw-redirect" title="Saint Gregory the Great">Saint Gregory the Great</a>─as recorded by his secretary or other church father authors, dictating their works to them.
</p><p>The dove also parallels the one that brought the olive branch to <a href="/wiki/Noah" title="Noah">Noah</a> after the deluge, as a symbol of peace.<sup id="cite_ref-Joel14_5-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Joel14-5">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>The book of Acts describes the Holy Spirit descending on the <a href="/wiki/Twelve_apostles" class="mw-redirect" title="Twelve apostles">apostles</a> at <a href="/wiki/Pentecost" title="Pentecost">Pentecost</a> in the form of a wind and tongues of fire resting over the apostles' heads. Based on the imagery in that account, the Holy Spirit is sometimes symbolized by a flame.<sup id="cite_ref-Eugene121_4-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Eugene121-4">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>There are also depictions of the Holy Spirit in the <a href="/wiki/Book_of_Genesis" title="Book of Genesis">book of Genesis</a>. In The <a href="/wiki/Vatican_Museums" title="Vatican Museums">Vatican</a> Museum in Rome is a carved stone sarcophagus depicting the Holy Trinity as three bearded men during the creation of <a href="/wiki/Eve" title="Eve">Eve</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-Robert68_6-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Robert68-6">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> The majority of early Christian art depicts The Holy Spirit in an anthropomorphic form as a human with two other Identical human figures representing <a href="/wiki/God_the_Father" title="God the Father">God the Father</a> and <a href="/wiki/Jesus_Christ" class="mw-redirect" title="Jesus Christ">Jesus Christ</a>. They either sit or they stand grouped closely together. This is used to portray the unity of The Godhead.<sup id="cite_ref-Jane546_7-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Jane546-7">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-Andrei54_8-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Andrei54-8">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>The Holy Spirit is represented in various artistic mediums such as stained glass windows and calligraphy.<sup id="cite_ref-Lois126_9-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Lois126-9">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<meta property="mw:PageProp/toc" />
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Gallery">Gallery</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Holy_Spirit_in_Christian_art&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Gallery"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<ul class="gallery mw-gallery-traditional">
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Pietro_Perugino_077.jpg" class="mw-file-description" title="Baptism of Christ by Pietro Perugino, circa 1498"><img alt="Baptism of Christ by Pietro Perugino, circa 1498" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/78/Pietro_Perugino_077.jpg/88px-Pietro_Perugino_077.jpg" decoding="async" width="88" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/78/Pietro_Perugino_077.jpg/132px-Pietro_Perugino_077.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/78/Pietro_Perugino_077.jpg/176px-Pietro_Perugino_077.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2328" data-file-height="3168" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext"><a href="/wiki/Baptism_of_Jesus" title="Baptism of Jesus">Baptism of Christ</a> by <a href="/wiki/Pietro_Perugino" title="Pietro Perugino">Pietro Perugino</a>, circa 1498</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Fra_Filippo_Lippi_002.jpg" class="mw-file-description" title="Scene by Filippo Lippi, 1459"><img alt="Scene by Filippo Lippi, 1459" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Fra_Filippo_Lippi_002.jpg/109px-Fra_Filippo_Lippi_002.jpg" decoding="async" width="109" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Fra_Filippo_Lippi_002.jpg/163px-Fra_Filippo_Lippi_002.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Fra_Filippo_Lippi_002.jpg/217px-Fra_Filippo_Lippi_002.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2024" data-file-height="2235" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext">Scene by <a href="/wiki/Filippo_Lippi" title="Filippo Lippi">Filippo Lippi</a>, 1459</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:The_Baptism_of_Christ_(Verrocchio_%26_Leonardo).jpg" class="mw-file-description" title="Both hands of God (relatively unusual) and the Holy Spirit as a dove in Baptism of Christ, by Verrocchio, 1472."><img alt="Both hands of God (relatively unusual) and the Holy Spirit as a dove in Baptism of Christ, by Verrocchio, 1472." src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/The_Baptism_of_Christ_%28Verrocchio_%26_Leonardo%29.jpg/102px-The_Baptism_of_Christ_%28Verrocchio_%26_Leonardo%29.jpg" decoding="async" width="102" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/The_Baptism_of_Christ_%28Verrocchio_%26_Leonardo%29.jpg/153px-The_Baptism_of_Christ_%28Verrocchio_%26_Leonardo%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/The_Baptism_of_Christ_%28Verrocchio_%26_Leonardo%29.jpg/204px-The_Baptism_of_Christ_%28Verrocchio_%26_Leonardo%29.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2652" data-file-height="3124" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext">Both <a href="/wiki/Hand_of_God_(art)" title="Hand of God (art)">hands of God</a> (relatively unusual) and the Holy Spirit as a dove in <a href="/wiki/The_Baptism_of_Christ_(Verrocchio)" class="mw-redirect" title="The Baptism of Christ (Verrocchio)"><i>Baptism of Christ</i>, by Verrocchio</a>, 1472.</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Zabrze_St._Joseph%27s_Church_window.jpg" class="mw-file-description" title="Stained glass window, Zabrze, Poland"><img alt="Stained glass window, Zabrze, Poland" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cd/Zabrze_St._Joseph%27s_Church_window.jpg/120px-Zabrze_St._Joseph%27s_Church_window.jpg" decoding="async" width="120" height="116" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cd/Zabrze_St._Joseph%27s_Church_window.jpg/180px-Zabrze_St._Joseph%27s_Church_window.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cd/Zabrze_St._Joseph%27s_Church_window.jpg/240px-Zabrze_St._Joseph%27s_Church_window.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1977" data-file-height="1908" /></a></span></div>
